+ Getting Started with Solar

++ Initial Installation

+++ Download and install via PEAR

<code type="bash">
$ pear channel-discover solarphp.com
$ pear install Solar/Solar-devel
...
</code>

+++ Set up the front-controller

<code type="bash">
$ cd /home/username/public_html
$ vi index.php
</code>

<code type="php">
// Path to PEAR libraries, where Solar is installed
set_include_path('/home/username/pear/php');

// Load and start Solar
require_once 'Solar.php';
Solar::start();

// Instantiate and run the front controller
$front = Solar::factory('Solar_Controller_Front');
$front->display();

// Done!
Solar::stop();
</code>


+++ Symlink (alias) to the public directory

<code type="bash">
$ cd /home/username/public_html
$ mkdir public
$ cd public
$ ln -s /home/username/pear/php/Solar/App/Public Solar
</code>


+++ Set up a minimal config file

<code type="bash">
$ cd /home/username/public_html
$ vi Solar.config.php
</code>

<code type="php">
$config = array();

// SQL connection
$config['Solar_Sql'] = array(
	'driver' => 'Solar_Sql_Driver_Mysql',
	'host'   => '127.0.0.1',
	'user'   => 'username',
	'pass'   => 'password',
	'name'   => 'database',
);

// Your front controller href
$config['Solar_Uri']['action'] = '/index.php';

// Your public directory href
$config['Solar_Uri']['public'] = '/public';

// Done!
return $config;
</code>
    
++ Browse to "Hello World"

``http://example.com/index.php/hello``


++ Move your config file outside the web root

<code type="bash">
$ cd /home/username/public_html
$ mv Solar.config.php /home/username
$ vi index.php
</code>

<code type="php">
// Path to PEAR libraries, where Solar is installed
set_include_path('/home/username/pear/php');

// Load and start Solar
require_once 'Solar.php';
Solar::start('/home/username/Solar.config.php');

// Instantiate and run the front controller
$front = Solar::factory('Solar_Controller_Front');
$front->display();

// Done!
Solar::stop();
</code>
